                <Content Chars="Mitaeme is an international auxiliary language (IAL)—a means of communication between speakers of various languages around the world. It is not meant to replace anyone’s native tongue but instead to serve as a tool for organization and collaboration between common people against the interests of nationalist, fascist, and capitalist powers."/>
                <para ParagraphEffectOffset="3.6" ParagraphEffectIndent="1" HasDropCap="0" Bullet="0" Numeration="0" NumerationFormat="0" NumerationName="&lt;local block&gt;" NumerationLevel="0" NumerationPrefix="" NumerationSuffix="." NumerationStart="1" NumerationOther="1" NumerationHigher="1"/>
                <para/>
                <Content Chars="Mitaeme is designed with simplicity and diversity in mind. It draws its vocabulary from all around the world, many words coming from the current top-twenty most-spoken languages: English, Mandarin Chinese, Hindustani, Spanish, Arabic, French, Bengali, Portuguese, Indonesian, Russian, German, Japanese, Nigerian Pidgin, Marathi, Vietnamese, Telugu, Swahili, and Hausa. In addition, it draws from a variety of other languages, including Turkish, Tagalog, Tamil, and Farsi."/>
                <para/>
                <para/>
                <Content Chars="The grammar of the language is based on the most common and easily-learned elements of these largest languages. There’s no need to memorize tables of conjugations or rare exceptions to rules: Mitaeme words never change form, and the grammar is straightforward yet flexible. Have fun with it!"/>
                <trail/>
            </StoryText>
        </PageObject>
